folder: Riverside Park & Between 76th and 83rd Streets (West)., Manhattan, NY
text:
Riverside Park: A set of 2 views from 83rd and 76th Streets, southward respectively showing marginal lands and the New York Central Railroad tracks. At 72nd Street the latter enters an open switching yard that is under the elevated vehicular highway shown and better known as the West Side Elevated Highway. Improvements to this, the Railroad and marginal lands will be completed in the Fall of 1937.

June 11, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Riverside Park - Between 76th and 83rd Streets (West).
